  "title": "feat(autocomplete): support panel customization",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for submitting a pull request!\r\n  Please provide enough information so that others can review your pull request.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Summary**\r\n\r\nThis PR adds support for panel customization, through templates in JS and a component prop in React.\r\n\r\nProps are:\r\n- `elements`: an key-based object to retrieve the rendered output of `recent` searches, `suggestions`, and indices (similar to [what Autocomplete provides](https://www.algolia.com/doc/ui-libraries/autocomplete/api-reference/autocomplete-js/autocomplete#param-render))\r\n- `indices`: the object returned by the autocomplete connector (doesn't include recent searches)\r\n\r\n### InstantSearch.js\r\n\r\n```js\r\nautocomplete({\r\n  // ...\r\n  templates: {\r\n    panel: ({ elements, indices }, { html }) => html`\r\n      <div class=\"left\">\r\n        ${elements.recent}\r\n        ${elements.suggestions}\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div class=\"right\">\r\n        ${elements.instant_search_movies}\r\n      </div>\r\n    `,\r\n  },\r\n}),\r\n```\r\n\r\n### React InstantSearch\r\n\r\n```jsx\r\n<Autocomplete\r\n  panelComponent={({ elements, indices }) => (\r\n    <>\r\n      <div className=\"left\">\r\n        {elements.recent}\r\n        {elements.suggestions}\r\n      </div>\r\n      <div className=\"right\">\r\n        {elements.instant_search_movies}\r\n      </div>\r\n    </>\r\n  )}\r\n/>\r\n```\r\n\r\nFX-3563",
